Overview
This project is a Library Management System designed to manage library operations like book inventory, member registration, issue and return of books, and fine calculation. The system ensures efficient management and tracking of library resources.

Here’s a sample README file for a Library Management System project:

Library Management System
Overview
This project is a Library Management System designed to manage library operations like book inventory, member registration, issue and return of books, and fine calculation. The system ensures efficient management and tracking of library resources.

How to Run the Project
Prerequisites
Programming Language: Java (JDK 17 or higher recommended)
Database: MySQL (or any other database as per configuration)
Build Tool: Maven (if applicable)
Steps to Run
Clone the Repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone <repository-url>  
cd library-management-system  
Configure the Database:

Import the provided library_db.sql file to set up the database schema and initial data.
Update the db.properties file in the project to match your database credentials.
Build the Project:
If using Maven:

bash
Copy code
mvn clean install  
Run the Application:

Compile and run the main file (LibraryManagement.java) using:
bash
Copy code
javac LibraryManagement.java  
java LibraryManagement  
Access the System:

If it’s a command-line application, follow the prompts on the terminal.
For web-based versions, visit http://localhost:<port> (e.g., http://localhost:8080) on your browser.
